title: Added correctErrorTypes to keep precise types in declaration signatures.
message:
Added correctErrorTypes to keep precise types in declaration signatures.

From the doc (https://kotlinlang.org/docs/reference/kapt.html)
Some annotation processors (such as AutoFactory) rely on precise types
in declaration signatures. By default, Kapt replaces every unknown type
(including types for the generated classes) to NonExistentClass, but you
can change this behavior. Add the additional flag to the build.gradle
file to enable error type inferring in stubs:
